Description: Fragment of concave lip of Attic black-glazed pottery Type C cup with handle root; wholly glazed; inscription cut on exterior.
Curator's comments: See Agora xii, nos. 407-413, fig. 4 and pl. 19, dated between 500 and 450 BC.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXIII, no. 90)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1656)
